Package: CohortIntelligence
Title: OHDSI-Native Cohort Exploration and Hypothesis Generation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("First", "Last", , "author@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Interactive cohort exploration workbench for OMOP CDM studies.
    Loads person-level OMOP domains (conditions, drugs, procedures,
    measurements, visits, observations, death), engineers patient-level feature
    matrices across time windows relative to cohort index dates, runs
    unsupervised machine learning (UMAP via 'uwot', k-means clustering via
    'cluster', isolation forest via 'isotree') to detect subgroups and
    out-of-distribution patients, ranks patients by review priority, and
    presents a Shiny dashboard with a reactive quilt plot (cohort-wide
    bird's-eye heatmap), trajectory viewer, anomaly explorer, hypothesis
    generation panel, and demographics tab. Designed for OHDSI studies using
    OMOP CDM v5.3/5.4. ML features require 'uwot', 'cluster', and 'isotree'
    (all on CRAN): install.packages(c('uwot', 'cluster', 'isotree')).
